import java.util.Scanner;
public class EvenOdd{
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        int a= sc.nextInt();
        System.out.println((a%2==0)?"Even":"Odd");
        sc.close();
    }}
here  System.out.println((a%2==0)?"Even":"Odd"); this means we are using ternary operator it means 
we use this for instead of if else in one line  code will be over (a%2==0)? this is condition "Even":"Odd" if yes it prints even if false it prints odd

